-- Windreich Names Former Areva Renewable Head to Post, Studies IPO
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2012-06-27T11:14:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/windreich-names-former-areva-renewable-head-to-post-studies-ipo.html
Windreich AG appointed the former
head of  Areva SA (AREVA) ’s renewable energy business as chief operating
officer as  Germany ’s largest developer of offshore wind farms
considers an initial public share offer.  Anil Srivastava, previously chief executive officer at
Areva Renewables, has “the expertise required for a potential
international IPO,” Willi Balz, chief executive officer at
Windreich, said today in an e-mailed statement.  Srivastava will lead technology, projects, international
sales as well as marketing for Windreich, the Wolfschlugen-based
company said. Windreich is preparing for a possible IPO of 25
percent of its shares this fall, Balz was cited as saying in an
interview this month in Die Welt.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
